<rss version="2.0"><channel><title>GitHub Trending: Puppet, Today</title><link>https://github.com/trending/puppet?since=daily</link><description>The top repositories on GitHub for puppet, measured daily</description><pubDate>Mon, 02 Dec 2019 01:06:09 GMT</pubDate><lastBuildDate>Mon, 02 Dec 2019 01:06:09 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>PyRSS2Gen-1.1.0</generator><docs>http://blogs.law.harvard.edu/tech/rss</docs><ttl>720</ttl><item><title>chrisboulton/puppet-ssl #1 in Puppet, Today</title><link>https://github.com/chrisboulton/puppet-ssl</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;[No description found.]&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;This repo does not have a README.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><author>chrisboulton</author><guid isPermaLink="false">https://github.com/chrisboulton/puppet-ssl</guid><pubDate>Mon, 02 Dec 2019 00:01:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>bisscuitt/puppet-module-conntrackd #2 in Puppet, Today</title><link>https://github.com/bisscuitt/puppet-module-conntrackd</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;Puppet module for manging conntrackd&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div id="readme" class="instapaper_body md" data-path="README.md"&gt;&lt;article class="markdown-body entry-content p-5" itemprop="text"&gt;&lt;h1&gt;&lt;a id="user-content-puppet-module-conntrackd" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#puppet-module-conntrackd"&gt;&lt;svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;puppet-module-conntrackd&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Puppet module to manage conntrackd.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Have a look at the main module class (&lt;tt&gt;init.pp&lt;/tt&gt;) to see what this
module does on a node plus usage examples.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a id="user-content-compatibility" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#compatibility"&gt;&lt;svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Compatibility&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Supports both ipv4 and ipv6, all conntrackd options and all sync modes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Compatible with Debian, Ubuntu and RedHat, Fedora, Centos, Scientific distros.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This module is designed to work with Puppet version 2.7.x or newer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a id="user-content-requirements" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#requirements"&gt;&lt;svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Requirements&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This module has got the following module dependencies:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;[stdlib]
Version 2.3.1 or newer. Standard library of useful resources by Puppet Labs.
It provides functions like validate_*(), is_*() and empty().
More information:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;stdlib at Puppet Forge &lt;a href="http://forge.puppetlabs.com/puppetlabs/stdlib" rel="nofollow"&gt;http://forge.puppetlabs.com/puppetlabs/stdlib&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The module source code &lt;a href="http://j.mp/w00GZr" rel="nofollow"&gt;http://j.mp/w00GZr&lt;/a&gt; to get a listing of available
functions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a id="user-content-usage-examples" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#usage-examples"&gt;&lt;svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Usage examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a id="user-content-install-and-manage-the-conntrackd-service" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#install-and-manage-the-conntrackd-service"&gt;&lt;svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Install and manage the conntrackd service&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;  class  { "conntrackd": }
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a id="user-content-multicast-sync-over-eth1-using-the-default-ftfw-sync-mode" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#multicast-sync-over-eth1-using-the-default-ftfw-sync-mode"&gt;&lt;svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Multicast Sync over eth1 using the default FTFW sync mode:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;  class { "conntrackd::config":
          protocol       =&amp;gt; 'Multicast',
          interface      =&amp;gt; 'eth1',
          ipv4_address   =&amp;gt; ${multicast_address},
          ipv4_interface =&amp;gt; ${ipaddress_eth1},
  }
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a id="user-content-udp-sync-over-eth2-using-the-alarm-sync-mode" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#udp-sync-over-eth2-using-the-alarm-sync-mode"&gt;&lt;svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;UDP Sync over eth2 using the ALARM sync mode:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;  class  { "conntrackd::config":
          sync_mode      =&amp;gt; 'ALARM',
          protocol       =&amp;gt; 'UDP',
          interface      =&amp;gt; 'eth2',
          ipv4_address   =&amp;gt; ${ipaddress_eth2},
          udp_ipv4_dest  =&amp;gt; ${other_remote_host},
  }
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a id="user-content-remove-service-package-and-configuration-of-conntrackd" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#remove-service-package-and-configuration-of-conntrackd"&gt;&lt;svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Remove service, package and configuration of conntrackd:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;  class  { "conntrackd":
          ensure         =&amp;gt; 'absent'
  }
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can find more examples in the examples dir.&lt;/p&gt;
